The paper deals with a communication channel model and its capacity analysis, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of matrix decompositions and multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems suggests that the paper may also belong to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The focus on MIMO systems and channel decomposition also suggests that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of structured codes and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
